Bring @honey{2%teaspoon} to room temperature. > Place in a bowl of warm water if crystallized.

Wash and dry produce. Drain and rinse @kidney beans{1}. Quarter @lime{1}. Gently crush @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce} in the bag. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; quarter lengthwise.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine ¾ of the @Tex-Mex paste{1%unit} (you'll use the rest in the next step) with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}. Stir in beans. Microwave for ~{1%minute}; stir in juice from one lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings). Set aside.

In a #large bowl{}, whisk together @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, honey, remaining Tex-Mex paste, juice from half the lime, and @olive oil{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings). > Tex-Mex paste is slightly spicy—if heat-sensitive, use less.

Wrap @flour tortillas{2} in damp paper towels; microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. Place tortillas on a clean work surface; spread @guacamole{4%tablespoon} across the bottom third of each tortilla. Top with Tex-Mex beans; sprinkle with half the @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} and half the tortilla chips. Place 1-2 lettuce leaves on chips (you'll use the rest for salad).

Fold bottom side of each tortilla up over filling, then fold over left and right sides toward the filling. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal. Divide wraps and remaining lettuce between #plates{}. Drizzle chile-lime dressing over lettuce; sprinkle with remaining Mexican cheese blend and remaining tortilla chips. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.